George Chereches is the sales engineer team lead for EMEA at OPSWAT. He has worked at OPSWAT for nearly five years, where he has been the technical lead for the business’s efforts to sell and deploy its Metadefender product line across the EMEA region. Chereches is experienced in delivering technical presentations, demonstrations, and webinars that help OPSWAT customers understand the full benefits of the Metadefender product range. In this conference session, Chereches speaks about the rising cybersecurity threats faced by financial services firms. He highlights why these organisations are at particular risk when it comes to these cybersecurity threats. Chereches then outlines the most common attack vectors that threat actors use to target financial services businesses like banks. He talks about the ways that businesses in the financial services sector can protect themselves against these attacks – including various industry best practices. Chereches concludes by explaining how OPSWAT helps its customers in the financial services sector protect themselves against a wide range of threat actors. Watch the full conference session with George Chereches below. 